@node Overview
@chapter Overview

@samp{org-msg-extras.el} extends @samp{org-msg}, the package that enables composing rich HTML emails using Org mode syntax. While @samp{org-msg} handles the core composition and export workflow, @samp{org-msg-extras.el} adds convenience features around the edges: managing multiple email signatures for different contexts, copying message bodies for external grammar checking, and improving the initial cursor placement when composing.

The package provides three categories of functionality:

@itemize
@item
@strong{Signature management.} User options for defining separate plain text and HTML signatures for personal and work email accounts (@ref{User options}).
@item
@strong{Message body operations.} Commands to copy the email body to the kill ring or to an external grammar checker (@ref{Message body operations}).
@item
@strong{Composition helpers.} Commands that position the cursor and adjust buffer state for a smoother composing experience (@ref{Composition helpers}).
@end itemize

The package depends on @samp{org-msg} and @samp{org-extras}.

