@node Message body operations
@section Message body operations

@findex org-msg-extras-kill-message
@findex org-msg-extras-open-in-grammarly
When composing an email in @samp{org-msg-edit-mode}, you may want to extract the message body for use elsewhere. The command @code{org-msg-extras-kill-message} copies the body of the current email to the Emacs kill ring, excluding the header section (everything up to and including the @samp{:END:} line of the properties drawer) and the signature block (starting at @samp{#+begin_signature}). If the current buffer is not in @code{org-msg-edit-mode}, the command signals a user error.

The command @code{org-msg-extras-open-in-grammarly} builds on @code{org-msg-extras-kill-message} by first copying the message body to the kill ring and then opening the Grammarly web editor in the default browser. You can then paste the message body into Grammarly for grammar and style checking. This provides a workaround for cases where the Grammarly Emacs integration is not working reliably.

@node Composition helpers
@section Composition helpers

@findex org-msg-extras-begin-compose
@findex org-msg-extras-end-of-meta-data
When you begin composing an email in @samp{org-msg}, the cursor may be positioned in the header area or after the signature, requiring manual navigation to the body. The command @code{org-msg-extras-begin-compose} moves point to the optimal position for starting to type the message body. If @code{org-msg-signature} is set, the command places point just before the signature. Otherwise, it calls @code{org-msg-extras-end-of-meta-data} to skip past the properties drawer and inserts a newline. It also calls @code{simple-extras-visible-mode-enhanced} to adjust buffer visibility for composing.

The command @code{org-msg-extras-end-of-meta-data} is a helper that advances point past consecutive Org property lines (lines matching @code{org-property-re}). It is used internally by @code{org-msg-extras-begin-compose} to skip the meta-data section at the top of the @samp{org-msg} buffer (@ref{Composition helpers}).

